The paper is about building and evaluating dialogue systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of state-of-the-art models and machine learning techniques, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also includes an analysis tool and an interactive tool, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
